- 'StyleMaster' is a brand name;
- 'Top 3 most expensive' refers to the highest-priced products;
- 'Size labels' are the sizes of the products, such as UK 4, UK 6;
- 'Clothing lines' are the collections or ranges to which the products belong.

- 'Woven a rich tapestry of tops and bottoms' refers to brands with products in the 'tops' and 'bottoms' categories;
- 'Robust stock presence since the dawn of the autumn season' refers to products with a last stock update on or after October 1, 2023;
- 'Stack up in terms of average stock levels and the number of unique threads' refers to the average stock quantity and the count of distinct product IDs.

- "jewels in the crown" refers to the most valuable or prominent items in a collection;
- "top three" refers to the highest-ranked items based on a specific metric (in this case, stock quantity);
- "clothing line" refers to a collection of clothing items designed and marketed together.

- 'Tops' refers to clothing items such as shirts, blouses, and t-shirts;
- 'Size measurements' include length, bust, waist, shoulder, and low hip measurements in centimeters;
- 'Total stock' is the sum of the stock quantities for each size of a product.

- "Running low in stock" refers to products with a stock quantity less than 10;
- "Size charts" include measurements such as length, bust, waist, shoulder, and low hip;
- "Detailed reports" include all relevant information about the product, such as its ID, name, category, material, color, price, brand, size label, measurements, line name, stock quantity, and location.

- 'FashionHub' is a well-known brand in the fashion industry;
- The 'clothing line' refers to a collection of clothing items designed under a specific theme or style;
- 'Cumulative stock' is the total stock accumulated over time at a specific location;
- 'Size chart' includes measurements like length, bust, waist, shoulder, and low hip to help customers find the right fit.

- 'Classic Collection' refers to a specific clothing line in the database;
- 'UK 4' is a size label used in the clothing industry;
- 'Top 5' indicates the highest ranked items based on stock quantity.
